article.headline: Chicago St 90, Valparaiso 76
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Royce Parran had 20 points and four of his teammates also scored in double figures as Chicago State beat Valparaiso 90-76 on Thursday night. Michael Henderson and Kevin Jones Jr. each had 15 points for Chicago State (3-14, 2-4 Mid-Continent Conference). Kourtney Calvin scored 13 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, while David Holston chipped in 11 points. The Cougars led 41-31 at the half. The Crusaders (11-5, 4-2 Mid-Con) were without three of their top seven players. Ron Howard led all scorers with 23 points, while Seth Colclasure had 20. Dan Oppland finished with 13 points.
